event.title: Nebraska Concealed Carry Permit Class Sunday 9:am to 5:pm
event.description:
8-9 hour class

 

The Nebraska Concealed Handgun Training will meet & exceed the requirements to get your Nebraska permit, or Iowa permit, as well as your Florida or Arizona non-resident permit.

Nebraska's resident permit will enable legal concealed carry in 30 states and Florida's non-resident permit is recognized 31 states while the Arizona non-resident permit allows you to carry in 31 states as well.  The list of states is slightly different for each permit so check out the reciprocity page for more details.

This is a State Of Nebraska Approved course taught by an NRA Certified Pistol Instructor in strict accordance with a state-approved lesson plan.

 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Requirement's for class attendance:

*Must be minimum 21 years of age.

* Must be a Nebraska Resident, or an Iowa Resident, for the Resident Concealed Carry application.

* NO convictions of a felony.

* NO Firearms related convictions in the past 10 years. (hunting without a license, etc.)

* NO convictions of any offense involving the use of alcohol or illegal controlled substances.

* NO convictions of any offense of domestic violence.

* NO adjudicated or apparent mental illness.

* NO physical impairments that would preclude you from safely operating and owning a handgun.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

To register for class, call 402-217-5000, or 402-325-8600

Or use the On-Line purchase link above.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

You can use your firearm, or if the instructors feel it prudent, one of the training facilities firearms will be provided for you.

* You will need to bring 100 rounds of factory ammunition (not reloads).  If further practice rounds are required to satisfy the instructor, these rounds will be provided to the student at no additional cost.

* You will need a cover garment like a outside shirt or coat.

* You will need a holster and belt or purse.

* You will need eye and ear protection.

***  You should have one, two, or three additional magazines for a semi auto pistol. (***not required, but it will make the range time flow better for you.)

 

 Leave ammo, and firearm in locked vehicle until instructed to bring them, unloaded, to the range.

NO AMMO IN THE CLASSROOM!

 

If you wish to be a promoter of this class and get a discount, bring along a friend and get 10% off.  In fact, you both get the discount, if you both register for the class. Enter 10off as a promo code

 

If you bring along two or more friends, you get 15% off.  Each of you get 15% off!  Enter promo code 15off

event.title: BTS: BUS PARTY to SKRILLEX @ CRICKET WIRELESS AMP (KANSAS CITY) 05-24-14 (SAT)
event.description:
Bus to Show

does

SKRILLEX

with

Dillon Francis

What So Not

Milo & Otis

at

Cricket Wireless Amphitheater (Bonner Springs)

 
 
Details:
  • Pick-Up Times and Locations can be found above, under Registration Type. If you don't see 'em, click More Info.
  • All BTS BusParties are Round-Trip unless otherwise noted (in the event or ticket title).
  • Bus to Show does not use tickets--regardless of which “Delivery Method” you select, you will not receive any. When you reserve, your name is recorded on our check-in list.
  • Bring your ID.
  • Check your email and voicemail often prior to departure for updates/changes. We’ll try not to make any (especially last minute).

How membership works:
  • If you are reserving for just yourself, membership enrollment is part of the checkout process, so you don't need to do anything extra.
  • If you are reserving for a group, every OTHER rider in your party MUST:
    • Either:
      Print & Sign This Membership Agreement
    • Or (preferably):
      E-Sign This Electronic Form (Save Trees!)

Waitlist:
  • If the bus you're after is full, keep checking back often, as we add buses frequently. You can also put your name on the waitlist and we'll do our best to contact you in the order you sign up if space becomes available.
 
 
The Fine Print
(Cue Fast Voice)

Reserving your spot early helps ensure that this bus will pop off. So does telling all your friends...and enemies. If we don't have enough reservations (10 - 20 riders), we might have to cancel this bus or combine it with another trip.  Please check your phone and email frequently prior to the event to make sure you are up to speed on any last-minute changes. We'll do our best to give you more than a day's notice of any changes. Trust us, we hate canceling buses, almost as much as you hate having them canceled, so let's work together and try to get everyone we know and don't know to ride safely to and from the show with us.


This trial membership includes reservations on the bus to this show and all other benefits of membership to The Basics Fund. Monthly members please click where it says "enter promotional code" and type your member password. To purchase a monthly membership please go here: http://tbfmembership.eventbrite.com/


Like the trial membership? You'll love the monthly--all you can handle TBF events and merch including free busparties on any TBF bus. Learn more about our memberships by clicking here.

 

Refund Policy:

  • Before the event:
    • We can refund your trial membership if you give us at least 48 hours notice.
    • If we cancel a bus due to low ridership.
    • If the refund request is within 48 hours of the event, and we have time and personnel available to do so, we will refund 50% of the Trial Membership fee and cancel your reservation.
  • After the event:
    • We are a membership-based non-profit. You are purchasing a membership to the organization, which includes access to its sober drivers, buses, DJs, frequent discounted or free show tickets, etc.
    • If you are purchasing a Trial Membership, this is an example of what it’s like to be a part of our organization. Usually it’s fantastic beyond imagination, but occasionally, things go wrong and maybe we are a little late, or a DJ doesn't show up, or the sound equipment malfunctions, etc. We do not offer refunds for these types of things.
    • Officially, we only offer refunds if we are not able to get you to and from the event with a sober ride. However, we are reasonable people, and we have a psychological complex where we need to be loved by every single person who meets us, so sometimes we refund trial memberships if something is extremely unsatisfactory.

 

  

Got more questions? You're not the first. Please read our ((FAQs)) before bombarding our poor, defenseless, swamped, and overwhelmed customer service representative with questions that have already been answered publicly.

 

Like the trial membership? Love the month-long. All-you-can-handle TBF events and merch including free BusParties on any TBF bus. ((ENROLL HERE)). Go ahead and reserve a spot on this bus first, then enroll in the monthly membership. We will issue you a membership code and refund any trial memberships you purchased for events that fall between the date you paid for your monthly membership and the end of the month you sign up for.

 

 

Want to throw your own events with Eventbrite while supporting The Basics Fund at no extra cost? Sweet. Click here to start your account and eventbrite will donate to us out of their cut.

ticket.description: Please bring everything you need to get your audio signal into our PA speakers.  They all have RCA inputs.  If you have your own speaker, please let us know.  This is a volunteer position.  DJ's are automatically members of The Basics Fund and therefore get to ride for free and bring a plus 1 on the bus.  If there are free show tickets available, DJs will be offered these first.  Also, we will be recording as many sets as possible for promotional release on through our soundcloud, and other online outlets.  You will receive a copy of the audio file that you can use and distribute however you choose.  Please plan on bringing a case for your gear that locks and a bike lock so that you can secure it inside the bus.

event.title: Drinks and Dancing Fridays and Saturdays at Soundbar (2014)
event.description:
If you are over 21, you are invited to Soundbar Friday and Saturday nights at 10pm for a VIP treat. Soundbar is located at 226 W Ontario st.  Your VIP password is "Sarah Emani".  After you register with my guest list at Soundbar you can mention "SARAH EMANI" at the door and get Free cover before 1130pm and VIP Hosted bar (beer, cocktails, wine etc. for each guest from 10 to1130pm).  If you would like to attend this event you must register/ Purchase tickets.  After you have purchased tickets I will take care of your registration and email you a confirmation message.  Your Registration includes

Fridays:

VIP all club access to Soundbar with unlimited guest list.  

Free Cover all night/ 1am on non event nights and VIP Hosted Bar (10-1130)pm

Free Registration for future events upon request.

Saturdays:

VIP all club access to Soundbar with unlimited guest list.  

Free Cover before 1130pm and VIP Hosted Bar (10-1130)pm

Email including a secret password that will be good for (FREE COVER before 12/ Discounted After) 

Free Registration for future events upon request.

You need not print tickets.  I will take care of this for you but you would still need to give the password "SARAH EMANI" at the door to be on my guestlist for this VIP deal before 1130pm.  If you would like to attend events regularly you can follow my face book "SARAH EMANI" where I post similar events.  

Must be 21 and over, Must follow proper dress code, must pass security. If you have a party of 15-20 guests I will give you an additional discount (25%) with my guest list.  Feel free to invite friends as many friends as you like, my guest list is unlimited.  Street/ Valet Parking is available for this event.  CTA riders can take Chicago Brown or #66 to Chicago and Franklin and walk a few blocks to Franklin and Ontario.  

 

 

Tickets can be replaced for another event upon request but No Refunds will be issued.
